    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Phonograph recordings made by cutting or embossing grooves into semi-soft materials that could be played back multiple times. These allowed for home, field, or broadcast recordings. Often referred to as “instantaneous discs," they are known to have been made in other forms such as cylindrical belts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
